    {
      "label": "Content description",
      "value": "Letter reused for writing exercises, signatures and/or pentrials. The writing exercises include the formulae: bi-sm all\u0101h al-ra\u1e25m\u0101n al-ra\u1e25\u012bm, ju\u02bfiltu fid\u0101\u02beaka, a\u1e6d\u0101la all\u0101h baq\u0101\u02beaka, l\u0101 il\u0101h ill\u0101 all\u0101h, l\u0101 shar\u012bk lahu. The basmala may be written in a calligraphic style. The writing is very cursive and contains many unconventional ligatures. The text on the recto and the verso consists of repetitions of greetings and blessings used in letter preceded by the basmala. Other phrases commonly used in letters are copied (l. 10; 5). In the text several Greek letters and signs appear."
    },
    {
      "label": "Diacritical dots",
      "value": "Diacritical dots are written in several places"
    }
